.TH NORN 1 "June 2026" "norn 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
norn \- Mainline DHT client for peer discovery and bootstrap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B norn
.RI [ OPTIONS ] " COMMAND " [ ARGS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B norn
is a command-line client for the Mainline DHT (Distributed Hash Table) based on BEP-5.
It provides peer discovery and bootstrap functionality for P2P applications.

The tool supports mutable and immutable items (BEP-44), read-only mode (BEP-43),
and secure peer discovery using Ed25519 keypairs.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B keygen
Generate an Ed25519 keypair and save it to
.I ~/.norn/key.pem
or the path specified by
.B --key
or the
.B NORN_KEY
environment variable.

Prints the public key (32 bytes, hex-encoded) to stdout on success.
.TP
.B get \fIKEY\fP
Retrieve a record from the DHT by its 64-character hex-encoded public key.

Requires a running DHT network or daemon.
.TP
.B set \fIKEY VALUE\fP
Store a signed record to the DHT.

Requires a keypair and running DHT network.
.TP
.B daemon
Run as a DHT daemon that responds to queries from other nodes.

Supports read-only mode (BEP-43) and private overlay mode.
.TP
.B version
Print version information.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-key \ \fIPATH\fP
Key file path. Default:
.I ~/.norn/key.pem
.TP
.BR \-\-port \ \fIPORT\fP
DHT port. Default: 6881
.TP
.BR \-\-timeout \ \fIMS\fP
Query timeout in milliseconds. Default: 5000
.TP
.BR \-\-log\-level \ \fILEVEL\fP
Log level:
.BR debug ,
.BR info ,
.BR warn ,
or
.BR error .
Default:
.BR info
.TP
.BR \-\-read\-only
Enable read-only mode (BEP-43). The daemon will not respond to queries.
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Show help message.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NORN_KEY
Default key file path. Overrides
.IR ~/.norn/key.pem .
.TP
.B NORN_PORT
Default DHT port. Overrides the compiled-in default (6881).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.norn/key.pem
Default Ed25519 keypair file. Created by
.BR keygen .
Permissions are set to 0600 (owner read/write only).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, missing key file, etc.)
.TP
.B 2
Network error (timeout, connection failure, etc.)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate a new keypair:
.B $ norn keygen
.br
c1eeee364c863115426bffe47b1ce23ca4b70a3ed6f8fbcf40ae2123661a1c4e

.TP
Store a record to the DHT:
.B $ norn set mykey "Hello, DHT!"

.TP
Retrieve a record from the DHT:
.B $ norn get c1eeee364c863115426bffe47b1ce23ca4b70a3ed6f8fbcf40ae2123661a1c4e

.TP
Run as a DHT daemon on port 6881:
.B $ norn daemon --port 6881

.TP
Run in read-only mode (BEP-43):
.B $ norn daemon --read-only

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bifrost (1),
.BR dht (1)

